  "datePublished": "2026-01-01",
  "description": "The median of a collection of values is the middle value when all values are arranged in order. Half the values fall below the median and half above — it splits the data into two equal halves. If you have five test scores (70, 80, 85, 90, 100), the median is 85, the third value. If you have six scores (70, 80, 85, 90, 95, 100), the median is the average of the third and fourth values: (85+90)/2=87.5(85 + 90)/2 = 87.5.\n",
